# module module

Renders a module scope declaration as an XML context wrapper. The MODULE type tells the model it is working inside a single logical file — a scoped implementation boundary, not a top-level service.

# entity Output

```markdown
<system_context type="MODULE"{{#name}} name="{{name}}"{{/name}}>

{{body}}

</system_context>
```

# rule

- name is optional. When present it must be camelCase and renders as the `name` attribute; when absent the attribute is omitted.
- Single-brace variable references in the body are resolved before this template executes — they become resolved names that tell the model which other modules or services this one connects to.
- The closing `</system_context>` tag must always be present on its own line with a blank line before it.
